    "Overall, they conclude that Copilot's design should be improved [41].The student perspective on program synthesizers including Copilot was gathered by Jayagopal et al. [42], who focused on its learnability.",
    "They observed and interviewed 22 novice programmers who worked with the respective systems, and evaluated the systems' design.",
    "Students, for example, reported that prompting is perceived as less confusing and more exciting than writing format specifications [42].Denny et al. [43] also investigated first year students' interactions (n=54) with the tool Promptly.",
    "Promptly was designed to teach students how to prompt GenAI tools based on predefined problems.",
    "It executes and tests the code generated by an LLM."
